  <description type="morphology">Plants 5–40 dm. Stems: thorns sparse to abundant; young twigs reddish brown-hairy, glabrescent. Leaves: stipules 3–8 mm; petiole 1–3 mm; blade oblanceolate or narrowly obovate, 2.5–4.5 × 0.5–1.2 cm, base cuneate, margins entire, rarely with minute teeth near apices, apex truncate or retuse, rarely rounded, abaxial surface brown-hairy, becoming glabrate and pale green, not glaucescent, adaxial glabrous. Inflorescences 3–4 cm diam. Pedicels 5–12 mm, sparsely brown-hairy. Flowers 8–10 mm diam.; hypanthium densely hairy; &lt;calyx brown- or yellowish brown-puberulent when young, glabrescent&gt;, sepals triangular, 1–1.3 mm, apex acute; petals suborbiculate, 3–4 mm, apex slightly emarginate. Pomes orange-red, 4–7 mm diam.; pedicels 5–13 mm.</description>
